        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Provide the package entry point for hierarchy level builders — modules that assign hierarchical nesting levels to document lines based on document type. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Package initialization for hierarchy_level_builders subpackage. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (package-level). \par \b Output\/ \:  Public symbols re-exported from hierarchy builder modules. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(8): <ref refid="namespacededoc_1_1structure__extractors" kindref="compound">dedoc.structure_extractors</ref>] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>All builders produce a consistent level assignment per line.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Builders are document-type-specific (law, diploma, TOC, TZ, headers). \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why a hierarchy builders subpackage? A: Hierarchy construction is the core structural inference step — isolating builders by document type keeps each strategy focused and testable. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added semantic template markup] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[Hierarchy building]: ClassifiedLines → HierarchyBuilder → LeveledLines → StructureConstructor </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
